	<h3><a href="/news/2888/why-we-swing-our-arms-when-we-walk#comment-51682" class="active">Arm Swinging</a></h3>	<div class="content"><!--paging_filter--><p>When I was in the Royal Air Force we were obliged to swing our arms shoulder high or elbow high.  The British style of drill appears very crisp and smart when done correctly.  Sometimes we shared parade grounds with the American Air Force and were amused to observe their much more casual marching style.   Now when I am running or jogging the arms held loosely bent also assist and when driving up hill, more vigorous use of the arms seems to help.<br />
Stanley   Northern Ireland</p>
